properties.name: Blue Ridge Parkway Route
properties.description: A 227 mile route (that follows 217 miles of the Blue Ridge Parkway in Virginia). Get more tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

properties.name: Galax, Virginia
properties.description:
Home of one of the most amazing gatherings of fiddle-playing musicians in the world each August!

More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America.

properties.name: Blue Ridge Music Center
properties.description:
The Blue Ridge Music Center - there's an interpretative center, an amphitheater for outdoor concerts and a nice loop trail. There's also a store with an outstanding selection of local music.

Visit the official site (http://www.blueridgemusiccenter.org/) for a schedule of evening performances or just time your arrival for around midday - local musicians perform most days (you can call ahead on (276) 236-5309).

More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

properties.name: Mabry Mill
properties.description:
Probably the most photographed site on the entire parkway, Mabry Mill offers the mill itself, a woodland trail and a very popular little cafe/restaurant.

More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

properties.name: Rocky Knob Cabins
properties.description:
Rocky Knob Cabins have changed little since they were built in the 1930s and make a wonderfully characterful place to spend a night.

Book ahead by calling 540-593-3503.

To get here, turn off the Parkway at milepoint 174 and head east on Hwy 758. Eventually it'll turn sharp right: here you need to turn left and, pretty much immediately, right onto the track that leads down to the cabins (it's signposted).

More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

properties.name: Roanoke River Overlook
properties.description:
Just south of the bridge, turn off into this car park and follow the short trail to Roanoke River Overlook.
More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

properties.name: Peaks of Otter Visitor Center
properties.description:
Peaks of Otter Lodge and Restaurant - a very picturesque setting looking out over Abbott Lake towards the appropriately named Sharp Top Mountain.

More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

properties.name: Blue Ridge Parkway - Milepost 0
properties.description:
Blue Ridge Parkway Milepost 0
The northern terminus of the Blue Ridge Parkway and starting point for the mileposts that position every attraction along its route.

More tips and advice on this route at RoadTrip America (http://www.roadtripamerica.com/forum/content.php?353-Galax-to-Rockfish-Gap-Virginia-on-the-Blue-Ridge-Parkway).

Download a guide - including descriptions of what to find at key milepoints - at the "brochure" (http://www.nps.gov/blri/planyourvisit/brochures.htm) page on the NPS web site.
